> > > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1
> > > 
> > > Hi. I know this is unrelated but what is this:
> > > "Using generated security password: 96497452-1ea5-4b06-a34e-4b96467f0b4b" ?
> > > 
> > > What is security password used for? Why is it generated in the container not within helm chart? Why it is outputed to logs?
> > 
> > Hi Krzysztof. Can I ask you where you are seeing this? I cannot see it in the logs of the Jenkins Jobs. Perhaps I missed it?
> 
> https://logs.onap.org/onap-integration/gating//125680-1/k8s/k8s/kubernetes-status/pod-onap-policy-clamp-cl-pf-ppnt-b58fb6775-7f2ff-policy-clamp-cl-pf-ppnt-logs.html

Ah yes, I see. This happens because including the spring-boot-starter-security dependency in your Spring Boot project will cause it to auto-generate the password if it is not specified in the application.properties or application.yaml. It will randomly generate a password and print it to the logs. This password is not actually used in the application at all. There is a fix on the way through got this also here: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/policy/clamp/+/125610 and here: https://gerrit.nordix.org/c/onap/oom/+/11285

I don't think they will allow changes at this time in istanbul and that can take time.   In any case, it seems to me why make things more difficult in istanbul, unless there is some problem that we are trying to correct.
